reviews.text: Very clean and tidy. Staff very helpful and courteous. Room is a reasonable size but bed is more like a double than a king size as booked. Free buffet every morning for members which is a wonderful bonus. Washing machine and dryer provided. Lovely green terrace to relax in and shopping center is connected to the inn which makes things easily accessible. Subway is only 5 minutes walk away.

I'm not sure why this hotel is an 'Express' rather than a regular Holiday Inn (technicalities I imagine) but it really doesn't feel like it's lacking much.

The staff are polite and helpful, the rooms are reasonably big for the cost and clean and have all of the basics I required.

There are token operated washers and dryers on the semi open air relaxation floor if you need to do any laundry.

The breakfast area is a short walk (under cover) to the opposite Crowne Plaza Hotel and has a decent enough variety.

There is a huge multi phase shopping centre that includes a cinema and number of grocery stores and also connects to a few other shopping centres as well as the metro system (with the two main stops eastward also having large shopping centres connected, but not quite as big). 

My only criticism is that although they have made some changes to the lifts that serve the floors and restaurants (connected to the shopping centre) on busy days/times it still gets too crowded - they need to keep a lift dedicated to hotel floors (unless a key card is used).

Additionally, it is located quite far from the usual tourist spots so bear that in mind as it will require frequent travel.

Rooms are all the same size, but for HK still on the bigger side. Not very generous with upgrades to elite status travelers. Breakfast is in the adjacent Crowne Plaza building. If similar price Crowne Plaza is a better upgrade. Crowd at the HIE tends to be mainland Chinese and typically traveling groups and hence very noisy.
Very convenient place, centralized.. With easy access to transportation.. Signing up as an IHG members gives you some little perks..

Great place. New building. Modern fitout. Friendly staff. Nice size rooms, clean, well presented, comfy beds. They have a green floor which is open air and there is exercise bikes, rowing machines that you can use while waiting for your washing to wash or dry (same floor). If Breakfast is included, you get to go the Crown Plaza for breakfast - added bonus.
